<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="316" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1410,1614]" pageId="11" pageNumber="316">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,284,1410,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="316">Discussion.</emphasis>
Some populations are darker, almost like 
<taxonomicName box="[761,947,1411,1435]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Folsomia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="11" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrioculata">
<emphasis box="[761,947,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="316">F. quadrioculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A few specimens were found which share two characters with 
<taxonomicName box="[378,537,1446,1471]" class="Entognatha" family="Isotomidae" genus="Folsomia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Collembola" pageId="11" pageNumber="316" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manolachei">
<emphasis box="[378,537,1446,1471]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="316">F. manolachei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: the second posterior ocellus is rudimental and posterior side of the manubrium has one ap-chaeta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="316" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1410,1614]" pageId="11" pageNumber="316">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,505,1518,1543]" pageId="11" pageNumber="316">Distribution and ecology.</emphasis>
A transholarctic species (
<bibRefCitation author="Babenko" box="[805,1120,1518,1542]" pageId="11" pageNumber="316" refString="Babenko, A. &amp; Fjellberg, A. (2006) Collembola septentrionale. A catalogue of springtails of the Arctic regions. Moscow: KMK Scientific Press Ltd., 190 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Babenko &amp; Fjellberg 
<number box="[1059,1120,1518,1542]" pageId="11" pageNumber="316" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). A common and eurytopic species. Inhabits all 
<typeStatus box="[377,436,1555,1579]" pageId="11" pageNumber="316">types</typeStatus>
of forests and alpine sites, often in dry conditions, but very rare in steppes (
<figureCitation box="[1280,1348,1554,1578]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1885,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,700,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,700,1864]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. The sampling sites in Buryatia: 1 – 2 — Vitim Plateau (1 — Konda Basin, 2 — Eravna Basin), 3 – 5 — Selenga Low Plateau (3 — Zagansky Range, 4 — vicinities of Schuch'ye Lake, 5 — vicinities of Karasinoye Lake), 6 – 8 — Barguzinsky Range (6 — Ust' - Barguzin, 7 — vicinities of Barguzin, 8 — upper flow of Barguzin River), 9 — Khamar-Daban Range, 10 — Tunkinskiye Gol'tsy Range, 11 — vicinities of Ulan-Ude, 12 — estuary of Selenga River, 13 — vicinities of Khorinsk, 14 — vicinities of Unnokent'evka, 15 –– Turka." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/254496/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="316">
Fig. 
<number box="[1332,1348,1554,1578]" pageId="11" pageNumber="316" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
: loc. 
<number pageId="11" pageNumber="316" value="2.25" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="1.0">1– 3, 5</number>
– 
<number box="[209,280,1590,1614]" pageId="11" pageNumber="316" value="12.15">12, 15</number>
).
</paragraph>
